author: Associated Press
title: Florida county commissioners vote against sanctuary status | Daily Mail Online
text: show ad Immigrant haven of Miami-Dade votes AGAINST sanctuary status - as protesters scream: 'shame on you' County commissioners in immigrant-rich Miami-Dade voted Friday to uphold their Cuban-born mayor's order to cooperate with federal immigration officials Florida's Miami-Dade County is the only U.S. county where more than half the population is foreign-born Commissioners backed the order of Mayor Carlos Gimenez that was delivered after the Trump administration threatened to withhold federal funding from so-called sanctuary cities In emotional public testimony, dozens spoke against the order Many of the people gathered at the meeting stood and shouted obscenities at the commissioners when they voted to uphold the mayor Published: 23:48 GMT, 17 February 2017 | Updated: 05:50 GMT, 18 February 2017 34 shares
